  "prompt": "Which is correct: \"a hour\" or \"an hour\"?",
  "response": "\"An hour\" is correct. \n\nEven though \"hour\" begins with the letter \"h\", it is pronounced with a silent \"h\", starting with a vowel sound (like \"our\"). Therefore, we use \"an\" before it, following the rule that \"an\" is used before words that begin with a vowel sound.\n\nExamples:\n- Correct: \"I will be there in an hour.\"\n- Incorrect: \"I will be there in a hour.\"",
